## ğŸ“˜ Background

**MyColorMind** is built to simplify working with colors in Python. It combines classical color theory and psychological color meanings to empower artists, UI/UX designers, and developers with tools for generating beautiful and meaningful color palettes.

---

## âœ¨ Features

âœ… Primary, Secondary, Tertiary color retrieval
âœ… Color wheel with relation functions: Complementary, Analogous, Triadic
âœ… Color mood-based palette suggestions (e.g., Happy, Calm)
âœ… Add custom mood palettes
âœ… Warm vs Cool color check
âœ… Psychological color meanings
âœ… HEX code for all known colors
âœ… Introspective method listing with `availableMethods()`
âœ… Fully object-oriented and extendable

---

## âš™ï¸ Installation

Install from PyPI (once published):

```bash
pip install --index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ colorMindAsad
